## 6. OCI-specific talking points (interview)

- **OKE** runs the workloads; **OCI Block Volume** backs OpenSearch data PVCs.
- **Load Balancers** are OCI LB as a Service — health checks must match **Service** ports and **Network Security Groups** / subnet rules.
- **OCI Search with OpenSearch** exists as a **managed** alternative; your setup is **self-managed OpenSearch on OKE** — trade-off: **full control vs operational burden** (upgrades, backups, ISM).
- **Observability of the observability stack:** monitor Vector buffer size, OpenSearch **cluster health**, **jvm heap**, **disk watermarks**, and **ingest lag**.

