## 7. Debugging mindset (platform)

| Symptom | Check |
|---------|--------|
| No documents in OpenSearch | Vector pods, ConfigMap sinks `endpoints`, auth, **index permissions** |
| OTLP refused | TLS mismatch, wrong LB IP, firewall, cert SAN |
| Hot nodes disk full | ISM delete/move, shard sizing, **watermark** errors in OpenSearch logs |
| Duplicate or missing logs | Idempotency at source; Vector **ack** settings; clock skew |

**Commands:**

```bash
kubectl get pods -n otel-vector
kubectl logs -n otel-vector sts/otel-vector --tail=100
kubectl get svc -n opensearch
kubectl describe pod -n jaeger -l app.kubernetes.io/component=collector
```

---

## 8. Security hardening (say this in senior interviews)

- Move OpenSearch credentials from **ConfigMap** to **Secret** and mount or env-inject.
- Turn on **TLS verification** (`verify_certificate: true`) for OpenSearch client when certs are trusted internally.
- Restrict **NetworkPolicy** so only Vector can reach OpenSearch **:9200**.
- **Rotate** credentials if they ever appeared in YAML dumps or tickets.

